        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I am using the Oracle Instant Client connecting to a remote RAC database. The RAC system has multiple hosts. TNSnames.ora entry needs \"LOADBALANCE clouth\", \"FAILOVER clouth\", hostnames.\nTherefore current PDO OCI module makes RAC TNSnames.ora entry too hard. \nSimply using \"oci:dbname=mydb\" (ZF1.0.3), I can connect RAC database.\nI think PDO OCI module must contain both functions (1.0.3 + 1.7.0).\n  * RAC = Real Application Cluster"
        },
